Guidelines to run simulations using the Python Version.

1.- Create a Python environment in Python 3.11 or in a higher version. This environment requires at least the following Python libraries:
 
	pysd
	numpy
	warnings
	time

2.- Case study selection

  - Select your case study
	- Copy and paste Policy.xlsx and Historical.xlsx files in the same folder as the model

3.- Open Policy.xlsx

	- Modify the intensities of the policies to create your own scenario.
	- Save the file with the applied changes.

4.- Open run_NEVERMORE_model.py

	- Modify the simulation period if you consider it necessary.
	- You can select the number of years to be stored in the results file.
	- Run the simulation.

5.- Results are provided in a unique file (csv and Excel) for the selected case study. The file includes all the selected variables among those available in the model.
